      "message": "I checked that none of CFLAGS, the contents of it (INLCUDES, DEFINES, EXTRA_DEFINES, STD, INC, DEBUG, VERSION, APPVERSION, TARGET, PROFILE, RBARCH, MEMORYSIZE, BUILDDATE, TOOLSDIR, FIRMWARE, GCCOPTS, SPEEXOPTS, IMXTOOLSDIR), RBCODEC_CFLAGS, nor SHARED_CFLAGS get modified by any of these included Makefiles.\n\nlibwmavoice/Makefile _does_ set CFLAGS, STD, and INC, but that is not being included here.\n\nBUILDDATE is a recursively-expanded variable that invokes a shell command, which would seem to be problematic if you wanted the same date more than once, but it only gets added to CFLAGS in firmware/test/fat/Makefile, which shouldn\u0027t matter here.\n\nI didn\u0027t do a complete audit of the build system, but I\u0027m pretty confident this won\u0027t change anything.",
